# OrcaSlicer Notes

These notes explain the key OrcaSlicer settings I had to change for my VZBot 330 setup.

This was one of the least clearly documented parts of the setup, and getting these values wrong caused confusion and movement issues.

## Important

These values are not universal.

They depend on:

* your printer configuration
* your homing behavior
* your actual reachable build area
* your offsets

Use these notes as a reference for **how to find your values**, not just what my values were.

---

## Printable Area

### My values

* X: 324 mm
* Y: 303 mm

### How I found them

After homing the printer, I manually moved the printhead using the screen controls.

To find the printable limits:

* move the printhead as far as it can safely print in **X**
* move the printhead as far as it can safely print in **Y**
* read the positions shown on the screen
* use those values as your printable area

For me, this resulted in:

* X = 324
* Y = 303

This is important because it was not clearly explained, and if these values are wrong, your usable print area will also be wrong.

---

## Origin

### My values

* X: -5 mm
* Y: 0 mm

### How I found them

After homing, the nozzle position in my setup was not sitting directly at the build plate origin in X.

Y stayed at 0 in my case, but X needed adjustment.

To find the origin:

* home the printer
* check where the nozzle is sitting relative to the actual build plate
* manually move the nozzle onto the real edge / start position of the printable area
* read the displayed position
* use that offset as your origin value

In my case:

* Y stayed at 0
* X had to be set to **-5**

I originally expected this to be positive, but for my setup the working value was negative.

The important part is not guessing the sign — it is testing what actually matches the physical printer behavior.

---

## Why this matters

This part was not properly explained in the documentation, and incorrect values here can cause:

* movement outside the intended area
* printhead crashes
* wrong print placement
* confusion during setup

---

## Machine Start G-code

;M104 S{first_layer_temperature[0]}       ; set nozzle temp uncomment to check preview
;M140 S{first_layer_bed_temperature[0]}   ; set bed temp uncomment to check preview
PRINT_START BED_TEMP={first_layer_bed_temperature[0]} EXTRUDER_TEMP={first_layer_temperature[0]}

This is the working machine start G-code I used in OrcaSlicer.

---

## Machine End G-code

PRINT_END    ; end script from macro

This is the machine end G-code I used in OrcaSlicer.

---

## Klipper-side start / end macros and printer config

See:

* `start_stop.cfg`
* `printer.cfg`

These are the printer-side macros used from the Klipper / Mainsail side.

This is a separate layer from the OrcaSlicer machine start / end G-code.

---

## Final note

The most important lesson here is:

do not assume the default values are correct, and do not assume the setup is clearly documented.

Home the machine, move it manually, read the real positions, and set the values based on what the printer actually does.
